    "Qwen2.5-VL-3B listwise rerank confuses ADC and DAC accuracy topics on dense parameter tables (Q06 top-1 flipped from ADC accuracy to DAC accuracy).",
    "Rerank is 5.4x slower per query (17s -> 94s) because the forward pass runs on GPU while the embedder runs on CPU.",
    "Moondream2 was the original Phase D target but has a custom API, pulls an external tokenizer (moondream/starmie-v1), and its custom vision encoder breaks at bnb 4-bit (layer_norm dtype mismatch). Abandoned in favour of Qwen2.5-VL-3B.",
    "The prewarm hook works correctly: the rerank worker spawns before the embedder, claims its ~2.5 GiB GPU slice cleanly, and handles the rerank request successfully. The quality drop is genuinely the model's listwise ranking, not an infrastructure issue."
  ],
